import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['total_casualties'] = data['wounds'] + data['other'] + data['disease']
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['total_casualties'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of casualties over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of casualties caused by wounds?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['total_casualties'] = data['wounds'] + data['other'] + data['disease']
    data['disease_percentage'] = (data['disease'] / data['total_casualties']) * 100
    
    plt.pie(data['disease_percentage'], labels=data['date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m'), autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the percentage of casualties caused by diseases compared to total casualties?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['total_casualties'] = data['wounds'] + data['other'] + data['disease']
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    monthly_avg = data.groupby('month')['total_casualties'].mean().reset_index()
    
    ax = monthly_avg.plot.bar(x='month', y='total_casualties', legend=False)
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Casualties per Month')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the average number of casualties per month?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
